juniDosProtectionMIB.name: juniDosProtectionMIB

revisions.description: Added new protocol type, atmDynamicIfPppData, to manage in JuniDosProtectionProtocolType.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniDosProtectionMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniDosProtectionMIB.description: The DOS Protection MIB for the Juniper E-Series product family. This MIB contains managed objects for the DOS Protection application. Management objects are provided to control and monitor the DOS protection application.

JuniDosProtectionProtocolType.name: JuniDosProtectionProtocolType
JuniDosProtectionProtocolType.description: The control protocols that are supported by the DOS protection application.

JuniDosProtectionPriorityType.name: JuniDosProtectionPriorityType
JuniDosProtectionPriorityType.description: The control priorities that are supported by the DOS protection application.

JuniDosProtectionProtocolState.name: JuniDosProtectionProtocolState
JuniDosProtectionProtocolState.description: The current state of a protocol.

JuniDosProtectionScfdsTableOverflowState.name: JuniDosProtectionScfdsTableOverflowState
JuniDosProtectionScfdsTableOverflowState.description: The current state of the suspicious flow table.

JuniDosProtectionProtocolPriorityType.name: JuniDosProtectionProtocolPriorityType
JuniDosProtectionProtocolPriorityType.description: The control priorities that are supported by the DOS protection application for each control processor

JuniDosProtectionProtocolCannedType.name: JuniDosProtectionProtocolCannedType
JuniDosProtectionProtocolCannedType.description: The available canned dos-protection-groups which can be used to set defaults into a user specified group.

JuniDosProtectionLayerId.name: JuniDosProtectionLayerId
JuniDosProtectionLayerId.description: The available interface types for which a profile entry may be defined.

JuniDosProtectionControlProcessorDestina.name: JuniDosProtectionControlProcessorDestination
JuniDosProtectionControlProcessorDestina.description: The available control processors to which a control protocol may be directed.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalState.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalState
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalState.description: Controls whether the suspicious control flow detection system is enabled or disabled. Setting the value to enable(1) enables the suspicious control flow detection system. Setting the value to disable(0) disables the system. When read this object returns the current state of the system.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalGrouping.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalGrouping
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalGrouping.description: When set to enable(1), the suspicious flow control system will group flows when resources are unavailable to treat each suspicious flow individually. When set to disable(0), this feature will be inhibited and the suspicious control flow system may not recognize all suspicious flows during a resource shortage. When read this object will return the current state of the object.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalClearAll.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalClearAll
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalClearAll.description: When set to clear(1), the suspicious control flow detection system is cleared. When set to ok(0), there is no effect and the suspicious control flow detection system is unchanged. By clearing the suspicious control flow detection system all flows are removed from the suspicious flow table. When read, always returns a value of ok(0).

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalDiscontinuit.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalDiscontinuityTime
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalDiscontinuit.description: The sysUpTime at which the counters were last re-initialized on any slot due to a restart.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalTableOverflo.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalTableOverflowState
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalTableOverflo.description: Indicates whether any module in the system is in under a resource shortage situation. A value of notOverflowingOrGrouping(1) indicates that there is no resource shortage on any module. A value of grouping(2) or overflowing(3) indicates that at least one module is suffering from a resource shortage, and has acted according to the state of the juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalGrouping object.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentSuspi.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentSuspiciousFlows
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentSuspi.description: The number of flows currently marked as suspicious.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberSuspic.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberSuspiciousFlows
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberSuspic.description: The number of suspicious flows seen since system restart.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentSuspi.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentSuspiciousFlowGroups
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentSuspi.description: The number of flow groups currently marked as suspicious.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberSuspic.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberSuspiciousFlowGroups
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberSuspic.description: The number of suspicius flow groups seen since system restart.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentFalse.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentFalseNegativeFlows
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalCurrentFalse.description: The number of flows currently falsely considered suspicious. A false negative indicates that the flow was seen as possibly suspicious, but did not pass all the tests to be considered suspicious. This is a normal condition of the system.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberFalseN.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberFalseNegativeFlows
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberFalseN.description: The number of flows falsely considered possibly suspicious seen since system restart.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberTableO.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberTableOverflows
juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalNumberTableO.description: The total number of times the system had a table overflow on any slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolTable.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolTable
juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolTable.description: The information for the DOS protection control protocols.

juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolEntry.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolEntry
juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolEntry.description: The information for an individual DOS protection control protocol.

juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolIndex.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolIndex
juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolIndex.description: The control protocol value for this entry.

juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolThreshold.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolThreshold
juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolThreshold.description: The threshold in packets per second for this control protocol. This is the rate at which a flow for this protocol is considered suspicious. Setting this object to zero will have the affect of excusing this protocol from suspicious control flow detection.

juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolLowThresho.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolLowThreshold
juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolLowThresho.description: The low threshold in packets per second for this control protocol . This is the rate at which a flow must fall below to in order return to the normal state, after having been marked suspicious. A low threshold of zero disables this functionality.

juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolBackoffTim.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolBackoffTime
juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolBackoffTim.description: The backoff time in seconds. A flow which is considered suspicious will be returned to normal after this amount of time regardless of the current rate of the flow. A backoff time of 0 disables this functionality.

juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolState.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolState
juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolState.description: The current state of the protocol. This object will return inTrouble(2) if any module in the system has reported that the protocol is currently being watched for suspicious flows. If no module reports that this protocol is being watched this object will return ok(1). A protocol is in trouble on a module when the sum of the rate for all flows for the protocol is over the limit for that protocol.

juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolTransition.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolTransitions
juniDosProtectionScfdsProtocolTransition.description: The number of transitions to 'inTrouble' that this control protocol has made.

juniDosProtectionDpgTable.name: juniDosProtectionDpgTable
juniDosProtectionDpgTable.description: The information for a dos-protection-group. A dos-protection-group defines a set of parameters that manage the handling of control protocols on the router.

juniDosProtectionDpgEntry.name: juniDosProtectionDpgEntry
juniDosProtectionDpgEntry.description: The information for an individual dos-protection-group.

juniDosProtectionDpgRowStatus.name: juniDosProtectionDpgRowStatus
juniDosProtectionDpgRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET. When read this always returns a value of active

juniDosProtectionDpgCanned.name: juniDosProtectionDpgCanned
juniDosProtectionDpgCanned.description: Sets the default values based for the dos-protection-group based on the values from the canned group. Can only be used to set a different group. Using the current group will result in no changes to the dos-protection-group.

juniDosProtectionDpgRevert.name: juniDosProtectionDpgRevert
juniDosProtectionDpgRevert.description: Revert this dos-protection-group to the canned values of the associated canned group by setting this object to revert(1). Reading this object will always return a value of no-revert(1)

juniDosProtectionDpgModified.name: juniDosProtectionDpgModified
juniDosProtectionDpgModified.description: When true is returned, some protocol or priority associated with this dos-protection-group, has been modified from the canned values associated with the group. When false is returned all settings associated with this dos-protection-group are at the defaults for the associated canned group.

juniDosProtectionDpgReferences.name: juniDosProtectionDpgReferences
juniDosProtectionDpgReferences.description: The number of references for this dos-protection-group. References include the number of interfaces currently associated with the group, as well as the number of profile references.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolTable.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolTable
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolTable.description: The information for the dos-protection-group control protocol table.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolEntry.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolEntry
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolEntry.description: The information for an individual dos-protection-group control protocol entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolName.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolName
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolName.description: The dos-protection-group name for this entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolProtocol.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolProtocol
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolProtocol.description: The dos-protection-group control protocol for this entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolBurst.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolBurst
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolBurst.description: The burst in packets for this control protocol in this dos-protection-group.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolDropProbabil.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolDropProbability
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolDropProbabil.description: The drop probability for suspect packets for this control protocol in this dos-protection-group. This is probability that a packet belonging to a suspicious flow will be dropped. A drop probability of less than 100 indicates that the user wishes to have some packets from a suspect flow reach the control processor.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolRate.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolRate
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolRate.description: The rate in packets per second for this control protocol in this dos-protection-group.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolSkipPriority.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolSkipPriorityRateLimiter
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolSkipPriority.description: When set to enable, this control protocol in this dos-protection-group will skip the priority rate limiter. When set to disable, the protocol will not skip the priority rate-limiter.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolWeight.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolWeight
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolWeight.description: The weight of this control protocol against others of the same priority in this dos-protection-group. The weight is used to determine the minimum rate and burst for the protocol within the priority group.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolPriority.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolPriority
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolPriority.description: The priority for the control protocol. Packets of this control protocol on interfaces referencing this dos-protection-group will be categorized into the priority indicated.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolModified.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolModified
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolModified.description: When true is returned, the values for this control protocol in this dos-protection-group have been modified from the canned values associated with the group. When false is returned all settings associated with this control protocol in this dos-protection-group are at the defaults for the associated canned group.

juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolDestination.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolDestination
juniDosProtectionDpgProtocolDestination.description: The destination processor for packets of this control protocol.

juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityTable.name: juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityTable
juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityTable.description: The information for a dos-protection-group priority table.

juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityEntry.name: juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityEntry
juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityEntry.description: The information for an individual dos-protection-group priority table

juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityName.name: juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityName
juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityName.description: The dos-proteciton-group name for this entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityBurst.name: juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityBurst
juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityBurst.description: The burst in packets for this priority in this dos-protection-group.

juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityOverSubscrip.name: juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityOverSubscriptionFactor
juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityOverSubscrip.description: The over-subscription factor for this priority in this dos-protection-group. This is used when calculating the minimum rates for control protocols that use this priority.

juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityRate.name: juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityRate
juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityRate.description: The rate in packets per second for this priority in this dos-protection-group.

juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityModified.name: juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityModified
juniDosProtectionDpgPriorityModified.description: When true is returned, the values for this priority in this dos-protection-group have been modified from the canned values associated with the group. When false is returned all settings associated with this priority in this dos-protection-group are at the defaults for the associated canned group.

juniDosProtectionDpgAttachTable.name: juniDosProtectionDpgAttachTable
juniDosProtectionDpgAttachTable.description: The information for the DOS protection attachment table.

juniDosProtectionDpgAttachEntry.name: juniDosProtectionDpgAttachEntry
juniDosProtectionDpgAttachEntry.description: The information for an individual DOS protection attachment entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgAttachIndex.name: juniDosProtectionDpgAttachIndex
juniDosProtectionDpgAttachIndex.description: The interface index for the attachment.

juniDosProtectionDpgAttachRowStatus.name: juniDosProtectionDpgAttachRowStatus
juniDosProtectionDpgAttachRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET. When read this always returns a value of active

juniDosProtectionDpgAttachName.name: juniDosProtectionDpgAttachName
juniDosProtectionDpgAttachName.description: The dos-protection-group for this entry. This is the dos-protection-group that is use by the interface.

juniDosProtectionDpgAttachConfigured.name: juniDosProtectionDpgAttachConfigured
juniDosProtectionDpgAttachConfigured.description: Indicates the configured status of the attachment. This object returns true when the attachment was statically configured, and returns false when the attachment was made via a profile attachment.

juniDosProtectionDpgProfileTable.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProfileTable
juniDosProtectionDpgProfileTable.description: The information for the DOS protection profile table.

juniDosProtectionDpgProfileEntry.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProfileEntry
juniDosProtectionDpgProfileEntry.description: The information for an individual DOS protection profile entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgProfileProfileId.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProfileProfileId
juniDosProtectionDpgProfileProfileId.description: The profile ID for the profile entry. The profile ID identifies which profile is being accessed. A value for this identifier is determined by locating or creating a profile name in the juniProfileNameTable

juniDosProtectionDpgProfileLayerId.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProfileLayerId
juniDosProtectionDpgProfileLayerId.description: The layer ID for the profile entry. The layer ID indicates which interface type is being accessed.

juniDosProtectionDpgProfileRowStatus.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProfileRowStatus
juniDosProtectionDpgProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET. When read this always returns a value of active

juniDosProtectionDpgProfileName.name: juniDosProtectionDpgProfileName
juniDosProtectionDpgProfileName.description: The dos-protection-group that is associated with this profile/interface-type. This profile will be attached when dynamic instances of the interface type are created that reference the specific profile.

juniDosProtectionCompliance.name: juniDosProtectionCompliance
juniDosProtectionCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper Dos Protection MIB. This was made obsolete with the addition of dos-protection-groups.

juniDosProtectionCompliance2.name: juniDosProtectionCompliance2
juniDosProtectionCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper Dos Protection MIB.

juniDosProtectionGroup.name: juniDosProtectionGroup
juniDosProtectionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of DOS protection application in a Juniper product. This object became obsolete with the addition of dos-protection-groups.

juniDosProtectionGroup2.name: juniDosProtectionGroup2
juniDosProtectionGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing management of DOS protection application in a Juniper product.
